name: Castle Park Orchard
short_description: Heritage fruit in the shadow of the Castle.
description: Established apple and pear trees are located in the lower park area near the Roman wall and river.

name: Cudmore Grove Samphire
description: The salt marshes here are a prime spot for gathering marsh samphire and sea aster (ensure you check tide times).

name: Incredible Edible Colchester - St Botolph's
short_description: Urban planters in the creative quarter.
description: Community-maintained planters near the station and priory ruins featuring herbs, chard, and kale.

name: High Woods Country Park Sweet Chestnuts
description: Large mature sweet chestnut trees are found throughout the ancient woodland sections of the park.

name: The Hythe Elder & Blackberries
description: The Colne riverside paths near the old port area are heavy with elder and blackberries.

name: Wivenhoe Trail Sloes
description: The trail connecting Colchester to Wivenhoe is lined with blackthorn bushes (sloes) and wild plum.

name: Gosbecks Archaeological Park Walnuts
description: Walnut trees can be found along the hedgerows bordering the Roman temple site.

name: Roman River Wild Garlic
description: The valley floor of the Roman River (near Friday Woods) is carpeted with wild garlic in spring.

name: Lexden Springs Rosehips
short_description: Wild rose on the meadow fringe.
description: The nature reserve hedgerows provide a good harvest of rosehips and haws.

name: Hilly Fields Orchard
description: A mix of apple and cherry trees planted for community use on this local nature reserve.

name: Berechurch Hall Hazelnuts
short_description: Hazels in the south of the city.
description: Public footpaths bordering the military land and wooded fringes are rich with hazel trees.

name: Brightlingsea Sea Beet
description: Sea beet grows abundantly on the shingle and sea walls near the promenade.

name: Abbey Field Elder
description: The perimeter of this massive open space is dotted with elder bushes for flowers and berries.

name: Greenstead Edible Planters
description: Raised beds near the local community hub featuring culinary herbs and seasonal vegetables.

name: Boxted Wild Plums
description: The lanes in this famous fruit-growing area often have wild bullace and plum trees on public verges.
